/*:
 * @target MZ
 * @plugindesc Player Weapon Action Motion Plugin - weapon motion / skill SE / swing overlay / fixed remote weapon overlay
 * @author CFpanda
 *
 * @help
 * ============================================================================
 * Plugin Introduction
 * ============================================================================
 * This plugin plays weapon-related attack motions for the player during map
 * battle actions.
 *
 * When the player uses a skill or attack:
 * - Reads the current weapon note tags.
 * - Plays a weapon motion or weapon overlay.
 * - Plays attack motion frames.
 * - Restores the original player graphic after the action.
 * - Supports skill sound effect note tags.
 *
 * ============================================================================
 * Weapon Note Tags
 * ============================================================================
 *
 * Character motion sheet:
 *
 * <motion:$Player_Swd01>
 *
 * Notes:
 * - The motion file is loaded from img/Actions/.
 * - Use a single-character sheet with "$" at the start of the filename.
 * - The sheet must follow RPG Maker MZ character format: 4 directions x 3 frames.
 *
 * Single-image melee swing overlay:
 *
 * <swingWeapon:Sword_01>
 * <swingHandle:38,38>
 *
 * Optional per-direction swing frame lists:
 *
 * <swingFrames2:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <swingFrames4:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <swingFrames6:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <swingFrames8:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 *
 * Remote weapon overlay:
 *
 * <remoteWeapon:Bow_01>
 * <remoteHandle:24,24>
 * <remoteLayer:front>
 *
 * 8-direction remote bow frame positions:
 *
 * <remoteFrames1:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames2:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames3:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames4:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames6:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames7:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames8:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 * <remoteFrames9:x,y,angle|x,y,angle|x,y,angle>
 *
 * Direction numbers:
 * - 1 = down-left diagonal shot
 * - 2 = down shot
 * - 3 = down-right diagonal shot
 * - 4 = left shot
 * - 6 = right shot
 * - 7 = up-left diagonal shot
 * - 8 = up shot
 * - 9 = up-right diagonal shot
 *
 * Each remoteFrames tag has 3 frames:
 * - Frame 1 uses Bow_01.
 * - Frame 2 uses Bow_01a.
 * - Frame 3 uses Bow_01.
 *
 * Each frame is:
 * x,y,angle
 *
 * Example:
 *
 * <remoteFrames6:16,-27,-20|21,-27,0|16,-27,20>
 *
 * Remote weapon image rules:
 * - Bow_01  = normal / undrawn image.
 * - Bow_01a = drawn image.
 * - The "a" suffix is automatic.
 * - Remote overlay is visible only during the remote attack action.
 * - Rotation is controlled directly by each remote frame angle.
 * - Mirroring is not forced; the bow angle should be tuned per direction.
 * - Frame 0: Bow_01 at fixed offset.
 * - Frame 1: Bow_01a moves forward slightly.
 * - Frame 2: Bow_01 returns to fixed offset.
 * - After the action, the overlay hides.
 *
 * Remote image files are loaded from img/Actions/.
 *
 * ============================================================================
 * Skill Note Tags
 * ============================================================================
 *
 * Weapon action trigger:
 *
 * <attackObject:slash>
 * <attackObject:arrow>
 * <attackObject:punch>
 *
 * User-front animation:
 *
 * <Animation:X>
 *
 * Skill sound effect:
 *
 * Short form:
 * <se:Slash1>
 *
 * Full form:
 * <se:Slash1,90,100,0>
 *
 * Format:
 * <se:fileName,volume,pitch,pan>
 *
 * Default values:
 * - volume: 90
 * - pitch: 100
 * - pan: 0
 *
 * ============================================================================
 * Default Behavior
 * ============================================================================
 * - If no weapon is equipped, $Player_Punch is used as the default character
 *   motion name.
 * - If no valid motion / swing / remote weapon note exists, no weapon action
 *   is played.
 *
 * ============================================================================
 * CF-BattleSystem Core Plugins
 * ============================================================================
 * Recommended order:
 * 1. Enemy Entity Plugin             CF_Enemy.js
 * 2. Attack Processing Plugin        CF_Attack.js
 * 3. Attack Object Handler           CF_AttackObject.js
 * 4. Player Weapon Motion Plugin     CF_PlayerActionMotion.js
 * 5. Skill Casting Link Plugin       CF_PlayerSkillCast.js
 * 6. Skill Hotbar UI Plugin          CF_BattleSkill_UI.js
 * 7. Enemy Sight / Aggro Plugin      CF_Eventsight.js
 * 8. Enemy Loot Plugin               CF_EnemyLoot.js
 *
 * Optional support plugins:
 * - Map HP / MP UI                   CF_HP.js
 * - Bow arrow dependency extension   CF_BowAmmoSystem.js
 * - Equipment visual system          CF_Equipment.js
 * - Position adjustment helper       CF_SetPosition.js
 * - Loot log helper                  CF_LootlogScroll.js
 * - Item hotbar helper               CF_MapToolBar
 * - Battle combo display             CF_BattleComboSystem
 *
 * ============================================================================
 * Copyright
